msContents.summary: C. Hermann Berendt's fair manuscript copy of Gabriel de San Buenaventura's 1684 grammar of the Maya language, the first printed Maya grammar, including a facsimile title page and the front matter in Spanish. Berendt also compiled an index to the grammar (p. 159-163).

supportDesc.extent: 83 leaves : 190 x 127 mm. bound to 197 x 136 mm
supportDesc.foliation: Paper, 83; [ii, 1-3], 4-143, 145-146, 148-163, [164, ii]; page numbers in ink, upper outer corners. The omission of 144 and 147 is an error in pagination; this record refers to pagination as it appears in the manuscript.

layoutDesc.layout: Written in 23 long lines on lined paper.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in the hand of C. Hermann Berendt, primarily in black ink, with corrections, additions, and marginalia in blue ink.

binding.p: Late 19th-century leather with minimal gold tooling; spine has Buenaventura, Ms., and a B at the tail of the spine for Berendt in gilt.

history.provenance: From the collection of C. Hermann Berendt, later acquired by Daniel Garrison Brinton (ex libris stamp on title page).
